    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The reason for this is because (perhaps historically) Truffle doesn't want to tie itself to NPM directly, so `truffle init` takes the approach to omit this file.\r\n\r\nAlso: what would we populate it with? Upon running `truffle init`, Truffle has no idea what you want your package name to be, the license, etc., so this (still) doesn't strike me as something we want as a feature enhancement... maybe we could add some messaging after `truffle init` to suggest \"hey, maybe you want to `npm init` also!\"?\r\n\r\nSince you're only asking the question here, would you mind closing this issue if your question is answered sufficiently, or reword this issue so that it represents something actionable? Maybe that just means adding messaging, or if you have clear requirements in mind for the contents of `package.json`, you could structure this as an enhancement request, and we can continue the discussion accordingly.\r\n\r\nThanks for bringing it up!",
