    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey @JimLynchCodes, we've been discussing this internally and are leaning towards being less opinionated and allowing devs to setup their own tooling. In addition, truffle doesn't need to install the `package.json` because `npm install <package> --save` will generate it.\n\nTeam consensus is still leaning towards adding messaging to the end of the `truffle init` output to suggest useful next commands.\n\nLastly, just for reference you can also use `truffle unbox <username>/<repo>` if you want to [create a box](https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/advanced/creating-a-truffle-box) for your own preferred configuration.\n\nThanks so much for all your thoughts / input on this! Also leaving it open so we can continue to have discussion on this as needed.",
